You are here: Salesforce Help > Docs > Service Cloud > Manage Call Centers

After you set up a call center, you can update the call center settings as your business needs change.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To import, view, edit, or delete a call center: Manage Call Centers

A call center corresponds to a single CTI system already in place at your organization. Users must be assigned to a call center record before they can use any Salesforce CRM Call Center features.

To view a list of created call centers, from Setup, enter Call Centers and select Call Centers. You can:

* View call center details
* Import a call center definition file
* Edit or delete a call center

When you delete a call center, all associated directory numbers are also deleted. Users must be reassigned to another call center to continue using Salesforce CRM Call Center features.
